From 12 December, Metrorail will be providing additional trains that will travel to beaches. CAPE TOWN - Metrorail is adjusting its train timetable for the holiday season.The annual festive season train service will commence on Monday (12 December).Metrorail s Riana Scott says as businesses and schools close for the year, they ll be providing additional trains that will travel to beaches. We ll reassign some trains, predominantly to Simon's Town and then also to the Winelands in the northern service area. (Edited by Zamangwane Shange)